\begin_layout Itemize
A route is a single continuous line of track that:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Contains at least two revenue centers (town, city, coalfield or off-board
 location) (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sec:Map-Explanation"

\end_inset

).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Can begin or end at a town, city, coalfield or off-board.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Must pass through a city containing one of the owning share company's station
 makers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Can pass through a city with an open station marker location.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Can use multiple entirely separate lines of track on the same tile.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Description
Note: Track tiles such as #16, #19, #20 etc and parts of #43, #44, #45 &
 #46 etc represent railway bridges and thus lines of track that do not intersect.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Can enter a city from one direction and exit in any other connected direction.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Additionally, a route cannot:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Cross the same hexagon-edge more than once.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Use the same piece of track on a track tile more than once (no matter how
 small the track section may be).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Pass through a city that doesn't have an open station marker location and
 doesn't contain owning the share company's station marker.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Run to or through the same revenue center more than once.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Description
Exception: But can run to or through both cities on 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

OO
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 track tiles or multiple cities in New York (G24) (see   
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "subsec:Track-types"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Note: The Canada off-board is comprised of two hexagons (A13 & A15).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Run to or though the Virginia Coalfields (K11) if the company doesn't own
 a coal token.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The routes of multiple trains run by the same share company during an Operating
 Round cannot share or re-use any line of track.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The routes can meet or cross at cities provided that they use entirely separate
 sections of track.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Off-board triangle connections are termini.
 Routes may not run to an off-board location via one black triangle and
 proceed back onto the board via another.
\end_layout

